<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 16 at 1:53AM CDT until April 16 at 10:00AM CDT by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 245 AM CDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN SEBASTIAN AND NORTHEASTERN LE FLORE COUNTIES...
At 153 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Cameron, moving
east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect damage
to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.
Locations in or near the path include...
Poteau...                         Hackett...
Hartford...                       Huntington...
Midland...                        Cameron...
Shady Point...                    Rock Island...
Patterson...                      Arkola...
Crossroads...                     Witcherville...
Dayton...                         Jenson...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.50 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
